6. . ( , for chi .)

chi_base_data <- mydata[,sapply(mydata, is.factor) | colnames(mydata) %in% c("stroke")]

chi_data <- data.frame(cate_var = colnames(chi_base_data)[1:7], chi = c(NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA,NA))


for(i in 1:7){
  chi_result <- chisq.test(table(chi_base_data[,i], chi_base_data$stroke), correct = F)
  chi_data[i,2] <- ifelse(chi_result$p.value < 0.05,"denied","accpet")
}

2. Catboost depth iteration grid search 5-fold CV .

set.seed(1234)

train_folds <- createFolds(mydata$stroke, k=5)

start <- Sys.time()
for(i in 1:nrow(logloss_cb)){
  cvacc <- NULL
  for(k in 1:5){
    cv_train = mydata[-train_folds[[k]], ]
    cv_test = mydata[train_folds[[k]], ]
    
    train_pool <- catboost.load_pool(data = cv_train[,1:6],
                   label = cv_train[,"stroke"],
                   cat_features = which(sapply(cv_train[,x], is.factor)))
    test_pool <- catboost.load_pool(data = cv_test[,1:6],
                   label = cv_test[,"stroke"],
                   cat_features = which(sapply(cv_test[,x], is.factor)))
    
    params <- list(iterations=logloss_cb[i,2],
               depth = logloss_cb[i,1],
               loss_function = 'Logloss',
               random_seed = 1234,
               train_dir = "CatBoost_output")
    
    CatBoost <- catboost.train(learn_pool = train_pool,
                               test_pool = test_pool,
                               params = params)
    test_error <- read.table("CatBoost_output/test_error.tsv", 
                             sep = '\t', 
                             header = TRUE)
    cvacc[k]<- test_error$Logloss
  }
  logloss_cb[i,3] <- mean(cvacc)
}

CatBoost_Runtime <- Sys.time() - start
CatBoost_Runtime
## Time difference of 44.50237 secs

Chapter 3. K-means Clustering

1. (age, avg_glucose_level, bmi) scale .

library(cluster)
library(factoextra)
## Welcome! Want to learn more? See two factoextra-related books at https://goo.gl/ve3WBa
scale_data <- mydata %>%
  select(age, avg_glucose_level, bmi)


scale_model <- scale_data

for(i in 1:3){
  min_value = min(scale_data[,i])
  max_value = max(scale_data[,i])
  scale_model[,i] = scale(scale_data[,i], center = min_value, scale = max_value - min_value)
}

summary(scale_model)
